lock - lock the screen
Executable: /bin/lock.sh
Alias: lock

DESCRIPTION
  Locks the terminal until the
  current user's password is
  re-entered. Useful for
  walking away from a running
  computer without logging
  out.

USAGE
  lock

NOTES
  Lock uses the active auth
  backend (local or network)
  to verify the password.
  If the login system is
  disabled, lock has no
  password to check against
  and returns immediately.

  Terminate (Ctrl+T) is
  ignored on the lock screen,
  but a Minecraft chunk
  reload or a server restart
  will still drop you back to
  init/login.

SEE ALSO
  login   - log in as a user
  passwd  - change a password
  halt    - shut down
